        <name>37.1.4.2 three-coin toss</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Find the expectation, variance and standard deviation of the number
of heads when tossing {@nCoins@} fair coins.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Give an exact answer, eg: \(\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Syntax hint: &lt;/strong&gt;\(\sqrt{2}\) can be entered using \(\texttt{sqrt(2)}\).&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;\(E(X) =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;\(V(X) =\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;\(\sigma(X) =\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]]
&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;The number of heads on \({@nCoins@}\) tosses of a fair coin follows a Binomial distribution with probability function \[f(x) = { {@nCoins@} \choose x } \left(\dfrac{1}{2}\right)^x \left(\dfrac{1}{2}\right)^{{@nCoins@}-x} = { {@nCoins@} \choose x&amp;nbsp;}&amp;nbsp; \dfrac{1}{2^{@nCoins@}}\quad \text{for} \quad x = 0, \ldots, {@nCoins@}.\]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol class="HELM_parts"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The expectation is \(\text{E}(X) = \sum_{x=0}^{@nCoins@} x f(x) =&amp;nbsp; 0\times f(0) + 1\times f(1) + \cdots + {@nCoins@}\times f({@nCoins@}) = {@ta1@}\).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;To calculate the variance, first we compute: 
\[\begin{align*}E(X^2) &amp;amp;= \sum_{x=0}^{@nCoins@} x^2 f(x) \\&amp;amp;=0^2 \times f(0) + 1^2 \times f(1) + \cdots + {@nCoins@}^2 \times f({@nCoins@})\\&amp;amp; = {@EX2@}.\end{align*}\]
It follows that \(\text{V}(X) = E(X^2)-E(X)^2 = {@EX2@} - \left({@ta1@}\right)^2={@ta2@}\).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Finally, the standard deviation is \(\sigma(X)=\sqrt{V(X)} = \sqrt{{@ta2@}} = {@ta3@}\).&lt;ol&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</generalfeedback>
